# PROJECT: rich-text-editor

## Goal
WYSIWYG rich text editor with Markdown as the storage format and Skia/skparagraph
for text layout and rendering. Media embedding via skparagraph placeholders.
UI via Slint with a custom Skia render notifier. Dual-mode: standalone GUI editor
and MCP server for live manipulation by Claude Desktop.

## Stack
- Language: Rust 2021
- UI: Slint (via slint-ui-templates library at ../RustUI)
- Text layout: skia-safe with textlayout feature (skparagraph)
- Markdown parse: pulldown-cmark
- Markdown serialize: custom AST-to-Markdown serializer
- Async: tokio (MCP server mode only)
- Serialization: serde + serde_yaml (YAML frontmatter)
- Syntax highlight: syntect
- Image decode: image crate
- MCP server: rmcp (stdio transport)
- Error handling: thiserror (domain) + anyhow (application)
- Logging: tracing + tracing-subscriber (stderr in MCP mode)

## Structure
- src: src/ (lib.rs + main.rs, binary name: rte)
- ui: ui/ (Slint files, imports from ../RustUI for shell/theme/tokens)
- doc: doc/ (frozen source documents — project.md, mcp.md)
- config: config/
- proj: proj/
- assets: assets/ (local media assets)

## Method
- Workflow: PROJECT -> FIXES -> TODO -> code -> test -> DONE
- Branching: feature branches, never commit to main
- Testing: cargo test, integration tests in tests/
- Linting: cargo clippy -D warnings, cargo fmt
- Deploy: binary release via cargo build --release

## Patterns
- document-model: All editing operates on Block/Inline AST, never on raw Markdown strings
- command-pattern: All mutations go through UndoStack::apply(cmd, doc) — no direct mutation
- render-notifier: Slint render notifier exposes Skia canvas; skparagraph renders there, not in Slint components
- mother-child: AppWindow (from slint-ui-templates) owns all state; children are stateless
- mcp-dual-mode: --mcp flag starts headless MCP server; no flag starts GUI
- ui-event-channel: MCP layer sends UiEvent via tokio::sync::mpsc to Slint UI thread
- placeholder-sync: Placeholder indices must stay synchronized with MediaManager asset list
- token-driven: All visual values come from slint-ui-templates tokens/theme — no literals

